The paper deals with designing a data structure for reporting the positions of distinct $\tau$-majorities within any range of an array, without storing the array. This involves techniques from data structures, information theory, coding theory, and computational complexity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
